The paper proposes a machine learning approach for predicting readmissions after coronary artery bypass graft surgery. It involves the use of Cox Proportional Hazard (CPH) survival regression and Deep Learning Neural Network (NN) representation of the CPH model, DeepSurv. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of predictive models and statistical analysis techniques, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential impact on healthcare costs, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
